asets of 306 genes, and combined each negative dataset with the positive dataset to train the classifier.    Classifier evaluation  As in previous works 18 , we used 5-fold cross-validation to evaluate the classifier, in which 20 percent of the whole data were left out as the test data and the remaining (80 percent) as the training data. Precision, recall, F1 score, and area under curve (AUC) were used as the measures to evaluate the classification performance. For each test dataset, we counted the numbers of true positives (TP), false negatives (FN), true negatives (TN) and false positives (FP). The formulas for calculating precision, recall, and F1 score were as following: \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
